</o:shapelayout></xml><![endif]--></head><body lang=DE link=blue vlink=purple><div class=WordSection1><p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN-US style='color:#222222;background:white'>I'm using Open MPI 1.6.5 to run OpenFOAM in parallel on several VMs on a cloud. mpirun hangs without any error messages. I think this is a firewall issue. Because when I open all the TCP ports(1-65535) in the security group of VMs, mpirun works well. However I was suggested to open as less ports as possible. So I have to limit MPI to run on a range of ports. I opened the port range 49990-50010 for MPI communication. And use command<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN-US style='color:#222222;background:white'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN-US style='color:#4F81BD;background:white'>mpirun --mca oob_tcp_dynamic_ports 49990-50010 -np 4 --hostfile machines simpleFoam &#8211;parallel</span><span lang=EN-US style='color:#222222;background:white'>. <o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN-US style='color:#222222;background:white'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN-US style='color:#222222;background:white'>But it still hangs. How can I specify a port range that OpenMPI will use? I appreciate any help you can provide.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN-US><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN-US style='mso-fareast-language:DE'>Best,<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN-US style='mso-fareast-language:DE'>Ping Wang</span><span lang=EN-US style='mso-fareast-language:EN-US'><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN-US style='mso-fareast-language:DE'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style='color:black'><img width=195 height=57 id="Grafik_x0020_1" src="cid:image001.png@01D1BC07.970F2480" alt="ascs_logo_300dpi"></span><span style='mso-fareast-language:DE'><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><b><span style='color:#4F81BD;mso-far